    <solution><p>We can make a substitution <m>t = e^{5x}\text{.}</m>  Then, we have <m>{4t - 2t^2 = 1}\text{.}</m>  We can re-write this as <m>{2t^2 - 4t + 1 = 0.}</m></p>
<p>We can use the quadratic formula:</p>
<p><me>t = \frac{4 \pm \sqrt{16 - 8}}{4} \approx 0.29289, 1.70711.</me></p>
<p>Recall that <m>t=e^{5x}\text{.}</m>  So, <m>e^{5x} \approx 0.29289</m> or <m>e^{5x} \approx 1.70711.</m> Solving gives <m>x \approx -0.24559</m> or <m>x \approx 0.10696.</m></p>
</solution>
